ShipTown

Postman collection OpenAPI spec

Introduction

API documentation for ShipTown

Base URL: https://shiptown.test

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

To authenticate requests, include an Authorization header with the value "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}".

All authenticated endpoints are marked with a requires authentication badge in the documentation below.

You can retrieve your token by visiting your dashboard and clicking Generate API Token.

Endpoints

PUT api/print/order/{order_number}/{view}

PUT
https://shiptown.test
/api/print/order/{order_number}/{view}
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

URL Parameters

order_number
integer
required
Example:
1
view
string
required
Example:
illum
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/print/order/1/illum';
$response = $client->put(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request PUT \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/print/order/1/illum" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/print/order/1/illum"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "PUT",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/print/order/1/illum'
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('PUT', url, headers=headers)
response.json()

POST api/shipments

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/shipments
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

order_id
string
required
Example:
aut
shipping_number
string
required
Example:
exercitationem
carrier
string
Example:
ut
service
string
Example:
eos
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/shipments';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'order_id' => 'aut',
            'shipping_number' => 'exercitationem',
            'carrier' => 'ut',
            'service' => 'eos',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/shipments" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"order_id\": \"aut\",
    \"shipping_number\": \"exercitationem\",
    \"carrier\": \"ut\",
    \"service\": \"eos\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/shipments"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "order_id": "aut",
    "shipping_number": "exercitationem",
    "carrier": "ut",
    "service": "eos"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/shipments'
payload = {
    "order_id": "aut",
    "shipping_number": "exercitationem",
    "carrier": "ut",
    "service": "eos"
}
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('POST', url, headers=headers, json=payload)
response.json()

POST api/orders

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/orders
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

order_number
string
required
Example:
voluptatum
label_template
string
products
object[]
required
sku
string
required
Example:
eveniet
name
string
required
Example:
labore
quantity
number
required
Example:
9979839
price
number
required
Example:
5311886.64
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/orders';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'order_number' => 'voluptatum',
            'products' => [
                [
                    'sku' => 'eveniet',
                    'name' => 'labore',
                    'quantity' => 9979839.0,
                    'price' => 5311886.64,
                ],
            ],
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/orders" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"order_number\": \"voluptatum\",
    \"products\": [
        {
            \"sku\": \"eveniet\",
            \"name\": \"labore\",
            \"quantity\": 9979839,
            \"price\": 5311886.64
        }
    ]
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/orders"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "order_number": "voluptatum",
    "products": [
        {
            "sku": "eveniet",
            "name": "labore",
            "quantity": 9979839,
            "price": 5311886.64
        }
    ]
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

    "order_number": "voluptatum",
    "products": [
        {
            "sku": "eveniet",

        }
    ]

  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'

response.json()

POST api/picklist/picks

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/picklist/picks
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

quantity_picked
number

This field is required when quantity_skipped_picking is not present.

Example:
3301283.05
quantity_skipped_picking
number

This field is required when quantity_picked is not present.

Example:
2.9
order_product_ids
number[]
Example:
[4826.611679]
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/picklist/picks';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'quantity_picked' => 3301283.05,
            'quantity_skipped_picking' => 2.9,
            'order_product_ids' => [
                4826.611679,
            ],
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/picklist/picks" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"quantity_picked\": 3301283.05,
    \"quantity_skipped_picking\": 2.9,
    \"order_product_ids\": [
        4826.611679
    ]
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/picklist/picks"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "quantity_picked": 3301283.05,
    "quantity_skipped_picking": 2.9,
    "order_product_ids": [
        4826.611679
    ]
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/picklist/picks'
payload = {
    "quantity_picked": 3301283.05,
    "quantity_skipped_picking": 2.9,
    "order_product_ids": [
        4826.611679
    ]
}
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('POST', url, headers=headers, json=payload)
response.json()

GET api/packlist/order

GET
https://shiptown.test
/api/packlist/order
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

filter
string
required
Example:
ut
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/packlist/order';
$response = $client->get(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'filter' => 'ut',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request GET \
    --get "https://shiptown.test/api/packlist/order" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"filter\": \"ut\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/packlist/order"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "filter": "ut"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

POST api/settings/user/me

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/settings/user/me
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

name
string
Example:
fugit
printer_id
number
Example:
441025413
address_label_template
string
Example:
sed
ask_for_shipping_number
boolean
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/settings/user/me';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'name' => 'fugit',
            'printer_id' => 441025413.0,
            'address_label_template' => 'sed',
            'ask_for_shipping_number' => false,
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/settings/user/me" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"name\": \"fugit\",
    \"printer_id\": 441025413,
    \"address_label_template\": \"sed\",
    \"ask_for_shipping_number\": false
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/settings/user/me"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "fugit",
    "printer_id": 441025413,
    "address_label_template": "sed",
    "ask_for_shipping_number": false
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

import json

);

    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

    "max_batch_size": 4,
    "max_order_age": 1
};

    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

    $url,

        'headers' => [

            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [

    "https://shiptown.test/api/data-collector-records" \

    --data "{
    \"data_collection_id\": \"recusandae\",
    \"inventory_id\": \"nihil\",

}"

    "https://shiptown.test/api/data-collector-records"
);

    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "data_collection_id": "recusandae",
    "inventory_id": "nihil",
    "product_id": "voluptatibus",
    "warehouse_code": "ipsum",
    "quantity_requested": 2.0803,
    "quantity_scanned": 3.79967227
};

    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

POST api/data-collector

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/data-collector
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

warehouse_id
string
required
Example:
voluptas
warehouse_code
string
required
Example:
perferendis
name
string
required
Example:
eum
custom_uuid
string
Example:
0032041f-1787-300b-818a-4c40a689f288
type
string
Must be one of:
  • App\Models\DataCollectionTransferIn
  • App\Models\DataCollectionTransferOut
  • App\Models\DataCollectionStocktake
  • App\Models\DataCollectionTransaction
Example:
App\Models\DataCollectionStocktake
destination_warehouse_id
integer
Example:
20
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/data-collector';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'warehouse_id' => 'voluptas',
            'warehouse_code' => 'perferendis',
            'name' => 'eum',
            'custom_uuid' => '0032041f-1787-300b-818a-4c40a689f288',
            'type' => 'App\\Models\\DataCollectionStocktake',
            'destination_warehouse_id' => 20,
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/data-collector" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"warehouse_id\": \"voluptas\",
    \"warehouse_code\": \"perferendis\",
    \"name\": \"eum\",
    \"custom_uuid\": \"0032041f-1787-300b-818a-4c40a689f288\",
    \"type\": \"App\\\\Models\\\\DataCollectionStocktake\",
    \"destination_warehouse_id\": 20
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/data-collector"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "warehouse_id": "voluptas",
    "warehouse_code": "perferendis",
    "name": "eum",
    "custom_uuid": "0032041f-1787-300b-818a-4c40a689f288",
    "type": "App\\Models\\DataCollectionStocktake",
    "destination_warehouse_id": 20
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

PUT api/data-collector/{id}

PUT
PATCH
https://shiptown.test
/api/data-collector/{id}
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

URL Parameters

id
string
required

The ID of the data collector.

Example:
cupiditate

Body Parameters

destination_warehouse_id
integer

This field is required when action is transfer_to_scanned.

Example:
5
action
string
Must be one of:
  • transfer_in_scanned
  • transfer_out_scanned
  • transfer_to_scanned
  • auto_scan_all_requested
  • transfer_between_warehouses
  • import_as_stocktake
Example:
transfer_to_scanned
custom_uuid
string
Example:
e9507cf6-0071-369b-b342-f1248e8cecda
name
string
Example:
similique

POST api/inventory-movements

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/inventory-movements
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

warehouse_id
integer
required
Example:
5
product_id
integer
required
Example:
18
quantity
number
required

Must not be one of 0.

Example:
20302.25701995
description
string
required

Must not be greater than 50 characters.

Example:
Officia asperiores ut ut voluptatem et odit dolores.
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/inventory-movements';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'warehouse_id' => 5,
            'product_id' => 18,
            'quantity' => 20302.25701995,
            'description' => 'Officia asperiores ut ut voluptatem et odit dolores.',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/inventory-movements" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"warehouse_id\": 5,
    \"product_id\": 18,
    \"quantity\": 20302.25701995,
    \"description\": \"Officia asperiores ut ut voluptatem et odit dolores.\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/inventory-movements"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "warehouse_id": 5,
    "product_id": 18,
    "quantity": 20302.25701995,
    "description": "Officia asperiores ut ut voluptatem et odit dolores."
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/inventory-movements'
payload = {
    "warehouse_id": 5,
    "product_id": 18,
    "quantity": 20302.25701995,
    "description": "Officia asperiores ut ut voluptatem et odit dolores."
}
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('POST', url, headers=headers, json=payload)
response.json()

POST api/jobs

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/jobs
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

job_id
number
required
Example:
8.5656752
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/jobs';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'job_id' => 8.5656752,
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/jobs" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"job_id\": 8.5656752
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/jobs"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

    "job_id": 8.5656752
};

    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

PUT api/mail-templates/{id}

PUT
PATCH
https://shiptown.test
/api/mail-templates/{id}
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

URL Parameters

id
integer
required

The ID of the mail template.

Example:
1

Body Parameters

subject
string
required

Must not be greater than 300 characters.

Example:
peflbbjrmxgjshauzriyd
html_template
string
required
Example:
libero
text_template
string
Example:
in
reply_to
string

Must be a valid email address.

Example:
morton29@example.net
to
string[]

Must be a valid email address.

Example:
["rice.zelma@example.net"]
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/mail-templates/1';
$response = $client->put(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'subject' => 'peflbbjrmxgjshauzriyd',
            'html_template' => 'libero',
            'text_template' => 'in',
            'reply_to' => 'morton29@example.net',
            'to' => [
                'rice.zelma@example.net',
            ],
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request PUT \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/mail-templates/1" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"subject\": \"peflbbjrmxgjshauzriyd\",
    \"html_template\": \"libero\",
    \"text_template\": \"in\",
    \"reply_to\": \"morton29@example.net\",
    \"to\": [
        \"rice.zelma@example.net\"
    ]
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/mail-templates/1"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "subject": "peflbbjrmxgjshauzriyd",
    "html_template": "libero",
    "text_template": "in",
    "reply_to": "morton29@example.net",
    "to": [
        "rice.zelma@example.net"
    ]
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "PUT",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/mail-templates/1'
payload = {
    "subject": "peflbbjrmxgjshauzriyd",
    "html_template": "libero",
    "text_template": "in",
    "reply_to": "morton29@example.net",
    "to": [
        "rice.zelma@example.net"
    ]
}
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('PUT', url, headers=headers, json=payload)
response.json()

GET api/modules

GET

/api/modules

$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/modules';
$response = $client->get(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

    --get "https://shiptown.test/api/modules" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(

);

const headers = {

};

    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example:

integer

boolean

Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/modules/1';
$response = $client->put(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'enabled' => true,
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request PUT \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/modules/1" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"enabled\": true
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/modules/1"
);

    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "enabled": true
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "PUT",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

POST api/modules/rms_api/connections

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/modules/rms_api/connections
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

location_id
string

This field is required when id is null.

url
string

This field is required when id is null. Must be a valid URL.

Example:
http://www.mraz.org/
username
string

This field is required when id is null.

password
string

This field is required when id is null.

warehouse_code
string

Must not be greater than 5 characters.

Example:
yr
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/modules/rms_api/connections';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'url' => 'http://www.mraz.org/',
            'warehouse_code' => 'yr',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/modules/rms_api/connections" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"url\": \"http:\\/\\/www.mraz.org\\/\",
    \"warehouse_code\": \"yr\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/modules/rms_api/connections"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "url": "http:\/\/www.mraz.org\/",
    "warehouse_code": "yr"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/modules/rms_api/connections'
payload = {
    "url": "http:\/\/www.mraz.org\/",
    "warehouse_code": "yr"
}
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('POST', url, headers=headers, json=payload)
response.json()

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/modules/webhooks/subscriptions'
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('GET', url, headers=headers)
response.json()

POST api/modules/webhooks/subscriptions

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/modules/webhooks/subscriptions
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

endpoint
string
required

Must start with one of https://.

Example:
https://psbb
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/modules/webhooks/subscriptions';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [

    --data "{
    \"order_id\": 459713165.21827906,
    \"comment\": \"aliquam\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/order/comments"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "order_id": 459713165.21827906,
    "comment": "aliquam"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

    method: "POST",
    headers,

}).then(response => response.json());

POST api/products

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/products
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

sku
string
required

Must not be greater than 50 characters.

Example:
hedtv
name
string
required

Must not be greater than 100 characters.

Example:
fpsaimqpdcxsosguwpgamsuoe
price
number
required
Example:
9.96
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/products';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'sku' => 'hedtv',
            'name' => 'fpsaimqpdcxsosguwpgamsuoe',
            'price' => 9.96,
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/products" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"sku\": \"hedtv\",
    \"name\": \"fpsaimqpdcxsosguwpgamsuoe\",
    \"price\": 9.96
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/products"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "sku": "hedtv",
    "name": "fpsaimqpdcxsosguwpgamsuoe",
    "price": 9.96
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/products'
payload = {
    "sku": "hedtv",
    "name": "fpsaimqpdcxsosguwpgamsuoe",
    "price": 9.96
}
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('POST', url, headers=headers, json=payload)
response.json()

GET api/reports/inventory

GET
https://shiptown.test
/api/reports/inventory
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/reports/inventory';
$response = $client->get(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request GET \
    --get "https://shiptown.test/api/reports/inventory" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/reports/inventory"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/reports/inventory'
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('GET', url, headers=headers)
response.json()

GET api/reports/picks

GET
https://shiptown.test
/api/reports/picks
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/reports/picks';
$response = $client->get(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request GET \
    --get "https://shiptown.test/api/reports/picks" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/reports/picks"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/reports/picks'
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('GET', url, headers=headers)
response.json()

Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/reports/stocktake-suggestions';
$response = $client->get(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request GET \
    --get "https://shiptown.test/api/reports/stocktake-suggestions" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/reports/stocktake-suggestions"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

}

GET api/restocking

GET
https://shiptown.test
/api/restocking
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/restocking';
$response = $client->get(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request GET \
    --get "https://shiptown.test/api/restocking" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/restocking"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/restocking'
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('GET', url, headers=headers)
response.json()

POST api/shipping-labels

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/shipping-labels
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

shipping_service_code
string
required
Example:
eius
order_id
string
required
Example:
consequatur
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/shipping-labels';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'shipping_service_code' => 'eius',
            'order_id' => 'consequatur',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/shipping-labels" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"shipping_service_code\": \"eius\",
    \"order_id\": \"consequatur\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/shipping-labels"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "shipping_service_code": "eius",
    "order_id": "consequatur"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/shipping-labels'
payload = {
    "shipping_service_code": "eius",
    "order_id": "consequatur"
}
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('POST', url, headers=headers, json=payload)
response.json()
